[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### What's Done Well
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Mathematical rigor with accessibility.** The "Defining Rising Risk Mathematically" section presents five distinct definitions with clear tradeoffs, making the concept accessible to non-technical readers while giving engineers the precision they need. This is the best section in the recipe.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Longitudinal modeling challenges.** The discussion of irregular observation intervals, informative missingness, confounding events, and regression to the mean is clinically accurate and reflects genuine operational experience. These are exactly the challenges that trip up teams building this for the first time.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Feature engineering specificity.** The trajectory features (score deltas, utilization acceleration, clinical marker trends, care engagement changes, new diagnosis velocity) are clinically appropriate and well-motivated. The multi-window approach is the right design choice.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Detection threshold transparency.** Exposing the thresholds as named constants with explanatory comments, and requiring 2+ converging signals to reduce false positives, demonstrates production-grade thinking.
